overview: From 2026-02-02 to 2026-02-03, elizaos/eliza had 0 new PRs (0 merged), 7 new issues, and 3 active contributors.

topIssues.title: [Agent] Eliza Character File & Prompt Engineering
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Improve Eliza's character file and prompts based on initial testing feedback.

## Background

Boris (Feb 2): "I've talked to Eliza only a little bit, just to test her out. I think she'll definitely need some edits in her character file, some more prompt engineering. She's a good start so far, but there's definitely stuff we're gonna have to work on. It'll be iterative."

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Review current character file responses
- [ ] Identify areas needing improvement
- [ ] Update character file with better prompts
- [ ] Add message examples (Ben has PRs for this)
- [ ] Test with Sonnet model
- [ ] Iterate based on user feedback

## Technical Notes

Ben mentioned:

* Currently using a different model, switching to Sonnet
* Two PRs coming that add message examples and change model to Sonnet
* "Huge difference in price between Sonnet and \[current model\]"

Boris mentioned Sonnet 5 coming out soon - good timing to test on Eliza if cheaper.

## Priority

**P2 - Iterative improvement**

topIssues.title: [Plugin] Integrate SMS/iMessage
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Set up blue text (iMessage) messaging capability for native iOS messaging experience. This is the most differentiating feature: "Eliza has a phone number."

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Inbound SMS/iMessage messages received by Eliza
- [ ] Outbound messages sent from Eliza appear as blue text (iMessage)
- [ ] Phone number provisioned for Eliza
- [ ] Message routing to correct user session
- [ ] Basic conversation flow working end-to-end

## Technical Notes

* Also have Twilio plugin as backup for SMS
* Reference Poke app's iMessage flow
* Critical differentiator: "Eliza has a phone number"
* This breaks the app container paradigm

## Priority

**P0 - Day 2-3**

topIssues.title: [Plugin] Integrate Telegram Plugin into Cloud
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Merge the Telegram plugin into the Cloud infrastructure so users can interact with Eliza via Telegram.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Telegram plugin PR merged to main branch
- [ ] Bot can receive and respond to messages in Telegram
- [ ] Multi-tenant support (each user gets their own Eliza session)
- [ ] Messages route to the correct user's agent instance
- [ ] Basic error handling and logging in place

## Technical Notes

* Extract from JG work (per meeting discussion)
* Ensure serverless compatibility
* Test with existing Cloud authentication
* PR already exists - needs review and merge

## Priority

**P0 - Day 2**
